Definition.WordDefinition: Ocarina \Oc`a*ri"na\, n. [Cf. It. carino pretty.] (Mus.) A kind of small simple wind instrument. [Webster 1913 Suppl.]
ocarina n : egg-shaped terra-cotta wind instrument with a mouthpiece and finger holes [syn: {sweet potato}]
